title: Ask HN: What will stop AI generated content from flooding the internet?
text:
Recently got into a discussion with a friend about how AI generated content allows for the mass production of unique lengthy content that is being and will be used to disseminate misinformation and advertisements.

My question is what protections are in place to stop people from using a mix of SEO and AI generation to flood the internet and our search results with machine produced content promoting some agenda.

Basically, what protections/strategies are being used to avoid our search results from being dominated by non-human written text.

Tell HN: I gave ChatGPT a question from Physics GRE and it answered it correctly
text:
This was the question: "A positive charge Q is located at a distance L above an infinite grounded conducting plane, as shown in the figure above. What is the total charge induced on the plane?"

I simply and copy and pasted it from a Physics GRE practice test without giving it the multiple choice answers [1].

The choices were:

(A) 2Q

(B) Q

(C) 0 <--- right answer

(D) -Q

(E) -2Q

Here is the answer it gave: "When a positive charge is placed a distance L above an infinite grounded conducting plane, the charge will cause an excess of positive charge to accumulate on the side of the plane closest to the charge, and a deficiency of positive charge on the opposite side of the plane. The total charge induced on the plane is the sum of the excess and deficiency of positive charge, which is equal to zero. Therefore, the total charge induced on the plane is zero."

[1] http://sites.apam.columbia.edu/courses/apph4903x/exam_GR0177.pdf
